1
00:00:05,152 --> 00:00:13,430
When that Vallabhacharya persisted, he said also, 
"I can give so many explanations

2
00:00:14,721 --> 00:00:16,835
of different Names of Krishna".

3
00:00:17,630 --> 00:00:21,029
[Quality Over Quantity]

4
00:00:21,629 --> 00:00:31,319
And Mahaprabhu said, "I only know... two: 
Yashodanandan and Shyamasundar.

5
00:00:33,647 --> 00:00:37,955
In fact I'm incapable of knowing more".

6
00:00:40,441 --> 00:00:42,083
What does that mean?

7
00:00:42,163 --> 00:00:44,709
He says, "nāmnām akāri bahudhā nija-sarva-śaktis" —

8
00:00:44,709 --> 00:00:48,094
"Krishna has unlimited names",
certainly not [two].

9
00:00:48,094 --> 00:00:52,004
But He is saying, "No, I only know two".

10
00:00:52,126 --> 00:00:54,586
He is talking about a particular quality.

11
00:00:56,696 --> 00:00:59,653
And also the implication is that

12
00:00:59,653 --> 00:01:02,130
if you are not focused on quality,

13
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:05,317
then you are going to be searching for quantity.

14
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:08,063
So Rupa Goswami advises,

15
00:01:08,063 --> 00:01:11,650
"Don't initiate many disciples, 
don't make many temples

16
00:01:11,650 --> 00:01:14,366
and don't read many books".

17
00:01:14,636 --> 00:01:24,809
He has told this would be... detrimental,

18
00:01:24,809 --> 00:01:29,374
detrimental to the culture of pure devotion.

